<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
            font-size: 12px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #000;
            padding: 60px 80px;
            background: white;
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #000;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .document-title {
            font-size: 24pt;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 15px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .date {
            text-align: right;
            font-style: italic;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #555;
        }

        .info-box {
            background: #f8f8f8;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 25px;
            margin: 30px 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .info-box h3 {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            font-size: 14px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .info-row {
            display: flex;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .info-label {
            font-weight: bold;
            width: 200px;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        .info-value {
            flex: 1;
        }

        .section {
            margin: 25px 0;
        }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 13px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .section-content {
            text-align: justify;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        ul {
            margin-left: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        strong {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="header">
        <div class="document-title">PRIVACY POLICY</div>
    </div>

    <!-- Date -->
    <div class="date">Last Updated: {{date}}</div>

    <!-- Business Information Box -->
    <div class="info-box">
        <h3>Business Information</h3>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Business Name:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{BusinessName}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Website:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{Website}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Contact Email:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{Email}}</div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-row">
            <div class="info-label">Business Address:</div>
            <div class="info-value">{{BusinessAddress}}</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This
            Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you visit
            our website {{Website}}, use our services, or interact with us in any way.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            By using our website or services, you consent to the data practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you
            do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not access or use our website or services.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 1 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We may collect the following types of information:
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>A. Personal Information You Provide to Us</strong>
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, mailing address</li>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Username, password, profile information</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Credit card details, billing address (processed securely through
                third-party payment processors)</li>
            <li><strong>Health Information:</strong> Medical history, injuries, physical limitations, emergency contact
                information (if you complete intake forms or waivers)</li>
            <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages, emails, feedback, reviews, or other communications you send to
                us</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>B. Information Collected Automatically</strong>
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system, device identifiers</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, links clicked, referring URLs</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies:</strong> Information collected through cookies, web beacons,
                and similar technologies (see Section 5 for more details)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>C. Information from Third Parties</strong>
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Social media platforms (if you connect your account or interact with us on social media)</li>
            <li>Payment processors and financial institutions</li>
            <li>Marketing and analytics partners</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 2 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">2. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>To Provide Services:</strong> Process registrations, bookings, payments, and deliver the services
                you request</li>
            <li><strong>To Communicate with You:</strong> Send confirmations, updates, newsletters, marketing materials,
                and respond to inquiries</li>
            <li><strong>To Improve Our Services:</strong> Analyze usage patterns, conduct research, and enhance user
                experience</li>
            <li><strong>To Ensure Safety:</strong> Monitor for fraud, security threats, and policy violations</li>
            <li><strong>To Comply with Legal Obligations:</strong> Fulfill legal requirements, respond to legal requests,
                and enforce our terms</li>
            <li><strong>To Personalize Your Experience:</strong> Tailor content, recommendations, and communications based
                on your preferences</li>
            <li><strong>For Marketing and Advertising:</strong> Send promotional materials, special offers, and targeted
                advertisements (you may opt out at any time)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 3 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">3. HOW WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information in the following circumstances:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third-party vendors who assist with payment processing, email
                delivery, hosting, analytics, customer support, and other business operations</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, sale of assets, or
                bankruptcy</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or government regulation, or to
                protect the rights, property, or safety of <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong>, our users, or others</li>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> When you explicitly authorize us to share your information</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 4 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">4. DATA RETENTION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy
            Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. When we no longer need your
            information, we will securely delete or anonymize it.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 5 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">5. COOKIES AND TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We use cookies, web beacons, pixels, and similar technologies to enhance your experience on our website.
            Cookies are small data files stored on your device that help us recognize you, remember your preferences, and
            analyze website traffic.
        </div>

        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>Types of Cookies We Use:</strong>
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Necessary for website functionality (e.g., login, shopping cart)</li>
            <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> Collect information about how you use our website to improve
                performance</li>
            <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences and settings</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Track your activity to deliver personalized advertisements</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            You can control cookies through your browser settings. Note that disabling cookies may affect website
            functionality.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 6 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">6. YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information (subject to legal exceptions)</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing communications at any time</li>
            <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your information in a machine-readable format</li>
            <li><strong>Object to Processing:</strong> Object to certain uses of your information</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at {{Email}}. We will respond to your request within a
            reasonable timeframe as required by applicable law.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 7 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">7. DATA SECURITY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your personal
            information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. These measures include:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of sensitive data (e.g., payment information)</li>
            <li>Secure servers and firewalls</li>
            <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
            <li>Access controls and authentication requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to
            protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 8 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">8. THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES AND SERVICES</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Our website may contain links to third-party websites, social media platforms, and services. We are not
            responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third parties. We encourage you to review their
            privacy policies before providing any personal information.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 9 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">9. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal
            information from children. If we become aware that we have collected information from a child without parental
            consent, we will take steps to delete such information promptly.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If you believe we have collected information from a child, please contact us at {{Email}}.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 10 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">10. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These
            countries may have different data protection laws. By using our services, you consent to the transfer of your
            information to the United States and other countries where we operate.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 11 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">11. CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS (CCPA)</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to know what personal information is collected, used, shared, or sold</li>
            <li>Right to delete personal information (subject to exceptions)</li>
            <li>Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell personal information)</li>
            <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising your privacy rights</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="section-content">
            To exercise these rights, contact us at {{Email}} or call {{Phone}}.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 12 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">12. EUROPEAN PRIVACY RIGHTS (GDPR)</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have rights under the General Data Protection
            Regulation (GDPR), including the rights outlined in Section 6 above.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We process your data based on:
        </div>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> You have given clear consent for us to process your information</li>
            <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing is necessary to fulfill our contract with you</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Processing is required by law</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> Processing is in our legitimate business interests and does not
                override your rights</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 13 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">13. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal
            requirements, or other factors. When we make changes, we will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of
            this policy.
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically. Your continued use of our services after changes
            are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 14 -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">14. CONTACT US</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please
            contact us:
        </div>
        <div class="section-content">
            <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong><br>
            {{BusinessAddress}}<br>
            Email: {{Email}}<br>
            Phone: {{Phone}}
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Acknowledgement -->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">ACKNOWLEDGEMENT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            By using our website and services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and
            consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described herein.
        </div>
    </div>

</body>

</html>